Hansal Mehta on 10 years of 'Shahid': A lot of gratitude for what it has given to all of us

PTI / Oct 18, 2023, 14:43 (IST)

Filmmaker Hansal Mehta celebrated the 10th anniversary of his film "Shahid" and expressed gratitude for the opportunities it brought him. The critically acclaimed biographical drama marked the beginning of Mehta's collaboration with actor Rajkumar Rao. "Shahid" is based on the life of lawyer and activist Shahid Azmi, who was assassinated in 2010. Mehta and Rao have since worked together on several successful films. Mehta's latest project, "The Buckingham Murders," starring Kareena Kapoor Khan, recently premiered at the 67th BFI London Film Festival.

When Sunil Grover had a fan-boy moment with 'Maine Pyaar Kiya' fame Bhagyashree

TIMESOFINDIA.COM / Oct 03, 2019, 13:30 (IST)

Talented actor Sunil Grover, who has impressed the masses with his last outing 'Bharat' had good Bollywood films like 'Ghajini', 'Gabbar Is Back', 'Heropanti', 'Pataakha' to his credits. However, the actor enjoys a huge fan following on small screen for his comic characters.

I always dreamt of being like Sridevi: Prabhleen Sandhu

TNN / May 06, 2014, 00:00 (IST)

Actress Prabhleen Sandhu is happy with the way her career is shaping up. She says, “I always dreamt of being like Sridevi. But coming from a small town in Punjab, I had no idea how to go about it.

Rajkummar Rao's Shahid drops on OTT: Discover how and where to watch the Hansal Mehta movie

Apr 11, 2024, 12:08 (IST)

Following "Bheed," Rajkummar Rao will star in a biopic about visually impaired industrialist Srikanth Bolla. The movie's trailer, titled "Srikanth," was released on April 10. Rao's performance received praise from everyone, but his wife, actress Patralekhaa, shared on Instagram that she was worried for him. She wrote that Rao once returned home with nearly a cracked rib and was close to losing his eyesight.

Rajkummar Rao's 'Shahid' finds no takers among OTT platforms, Hansal Mehta says, 'It is a tragedy for Shahid Azmi'

etimes.in / Feb 10, 2022, 13:44 (IST)

In a series of tweets posted last night, filmmaker Hansal Mehta expressed his thoughts on his 2013 release 'Shahid' not being streamed on any OTT platform. "Sad that #Shahid is not on any OTT platform. I have no idea who owns the rights to the film anymore and where it’s original version even is. It is a personal tragedy for me and for all those who toiled to make this film against all odds. It is a tragedy for Shahid Azmi," he wrote.

Ludhiana youth in first Punjabi 3D film

TNN / May 14, 2012, 03:28 (IST)

Model-turned-actor Jimmy Sharma is home these days working on his Punjabi feature film Khauf, which would be the first Punjabi 3D feature film, he says. Jimmy is also awaiting the release of his other film Rahe Chardikala Punjab Di.
